headline.main: 35TH ST. HAS FETE FOR AID TO BRITAIN; 6-Hour Carnival Held Near 7th Ave. Draws Isaacs and a Crowd of 20,000 $25,000 IS OBTAINED Dress Industry Workers Get Half Holiday -- Celebrities and Jitterbugs Take Over

lead_paragraph: A six-hour carnival, "too good to interrupt," in the opinion of Borough President Isaacs, was held yesterday in the heart of the garment district Roped off to traffic, Thirty-fifth Street, between Seventh and Eighth Avenues, welcomed an army of celebrities and found itself temporarily transformed into a ballroom for jitterbugs.
abstract: Brit-Amer Ambulance Corps carnival benefit, N Y C
